  <summary>Collect, organize, cite, and share research</summary>
  <description>
    <p>**This wrapper is not verified by, affiliated with, or supported by the Zotero project.**</p>
    <p>**Please report issues with this Flatpak in the manifest issue tracker instead of the Zotero Forums.**</p>
    <p>Zotero is a tool for managing references and research materials. It helps to collect bibliographic data, organize files, and generate citations in a wide range of formats.</p>
    <p>Main Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Save references and metadata directly from library catalogs, databases and websites using the Zotero browser connector.</li>
      <li>Organize books, articles, and web pages and attach notes, tags, and files.</li>
      <li>Annotate PDF, EPUB and HTML files with the integrated readers.</li>
      <li>Create citations and bibliographies in popular office suites using thousands of available citation styles.</li>
      <li>Import and export in common formats such as BibTeX, RIS, EndNote and Wikipedia Citation Templates.</li>
      <li>Extend the built-in functionality using plugins.</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
